            <div type="translation" resp="part:reda part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1"> 		
                    <supplied reason="lost">Prosperity!</supplied> Fortune!
                </p>
                
                <p n="1-4">
                   This is the 20th year of king Kulottuṅga Cōḻa. 
                </p>
                <p n="4-13">
                    We, the temple administrators in the temple of this god, <supplied reason="subaudible">have given the rights to sing</supplied> the closing stanza <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaṭai kāppu</foreign></supplied> of the <title>tiruvempāvai</title>, to Kulottoṅga Cōḻa Māṇikkam, alias Uṭaiyanācci<note>There is a village less than 20km. to the northwest of Nallūr that bears this exact name.</note>, daughter of Tiruvakampaṭi Naṅkai, alias Peṟṟi, a <foreign>tēvaraṭiyāḷ</foreign> in the temple of the Lord Nalla Nāyaṉār.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We, these temple administrators, have granted the hereditary rights <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kāṇi</foreign></supplied> to her after accepting <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>kaikkoṇṭu</foreign></supplied> the gold<note>The amount of gold is lost.</note> estipulated as price <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>vilai āka</foreign></supplied> and engraving it on stone.
                </p>
            </div>
            
